OL,5,F"We went after a storm in the Channel
OL,6,Fand I went over about two weeks
OL,7,Fafterwards."
OL,9,FMr Parker remembers landing on Sword
OL,10,FBeach via a larger ship which needed
OL,11,Fto wait for a tide.
OL,13,FThe first job for his comrades was to
OL,14,Ffind somewhere to base themselves.
OL,16,FMr Parker added: "We had to dig in as
OL,17,Fquick as we could and make a defensive
OL,18,Fposition. A machine gun post as well.
OL,20,F"And be up at half past four in the
OL,21,Fmorning in case of a German attack."
