OL,5,FThat air bombardment never came, and
OL,6,Fthe job he and others did, was to fix
OL,7,Fships and in particular - landing
OL,8,Fcraft that had got stuck in the sand
OL,9,For shallow water.
OL,11,F"People were stuck in the water and
OL,12,Fcouldn't start their landing craft -
OL,13,For we had to get men out of
OL,14,Fsomewhere," he said.
OL,16,F"We did all the odd jobs. And there
OL,17,Fwere a lot of troops in Normandy
OL,18,Fwaiting to go, waiting for the
OL,19,Fbreakthrough.
